## 🌟 Overview

FitTrack is a **full-stack MERN web application** built for modern gym management. It combines a polished public website, a personalized member dashboard, and a powerful admin panel — all in a sleek black & red theme.

The system supports **3 branches** (Colombo 7, Moors, Ja Ela), multiple membership plans, AI-powered fitness coaching, class scheduling, media management, and real-time analytics.

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) v18+
- [MongoDB Atlas](https://mongodb.com/atlas) account or local MongoDB
- npm or yarn

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/fittrack.git
cd fittrack
```

### 2. Frontend Setup

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```
> Runs on `http://localhost:5173`

### 3. Backend Setup

```bash
cd server
npm install
npm start
```
> Runs on `http://localhost:5000`

### 4. Default Admin Login

| Field    | Value                    |
|----------|--------------------------|
| Email    | `admin@fittrack.com`     |
| Password | `admin1234`              |
| Role     | Admin                    |

### 5. Default Member Login

| Field    | Value              |
|----------|--------------------|
| Email    | `john@gmail.com`   |
| Password | `john1234`         |
| Role     | User               |

> **Note:** To set a user as admin, open MongoDB Compass → find the user → set `role: "admin"` manually.

